# {{product_name_pascal}} — Design System

Generated by Ulak OS `/ulak-scaffold` on {{year}}. Scaffolded with a reference brand design system from `VoltAgent/awesome-design-md` to give the frontend a coherent starting identity — not to copy the brand, but to inherit its discipline.

## Reference brand

**Brand**: `{{design_reference}}` (from awesome-design-md)
**Upstream**: https://github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md/tree/main/design-md/{{design_reference}}
**External DESIGN detail**: https://getdesign.md/{{design_reference}}/design-md

## What we inherit

From `{{design_reference}}` we adopt (at scaffold time — later evolution is free):

- **Typography scale** — heading hierarchy (H1→H6) + body sizes + line-height system
- **Color palette** — primary, accent, neutral grays, success, warning, danger
- **Spacing rhythm** — base unit + scale (4px / 8px / 16px / 24px / 32px / 48px / 64px)
- **Border radius** — button / card / input / modal standards
- **Elevation / shadow** — surface layers (flat / raised / overlay / modal)
- **Motion language** — transition durations + easing curves
- **Component mental model** — how buttons / inputs / cards / dialogs feel in this brand

## What we DON'T inherit

- Brand logo, logomark, wordmark
- Brand-specific illustrations / photography
- Product-specific layouts (their homepage is not ours)
- Proprietary typefaces (we pick a similar-feel open-source alternative)

## Project-specific overrides

The scaffolder creates a **Master + per-page override** design-system artefact pair (per `docs/runtime/design-system-architect.md` AG-EXT-01 pattern):

- **Master**: `reports/current/design-system/MASTER.md` — global tokens + standards + intent
- **Per-page**: `reports/current/design-system/pages/<page-slug>.md` — page-scoped deviations with rationale

At commit 1 the Master is seeded from `{{design_reference}}` and any project-color overrides you specified at scaffold time. Pages are empty until the design-system-architect agent runs.

## Token files

- `tailwind.config.ts` — color palette + spacing + radius tokens derived from the reference
- `app/globals.css` — font loading + base text styles
- `lib/design-tokens.ts` — typed access to tokens for component variants

## Using this DESIGN.md

When briefing an AI coding agent (Claude / Cursor / Gemini) to build a UI component:

```
Read DESIGN.md. Build a <component> that matches the visual language of the
reference brand, using the Master + per-page override context from
reports/current/design-system/. Avoid generic Tailwind + shadcn defaults —
the reference brand is the starting point for our voice.
```

## Refreshing the reference

The brand reference can be refreshed (e.g., when you want to explore a different brand):

```bash
# From the Ulak OS repo directory:
bash scripts/fetch-design-references.sh <new-brand>

# Then copy the fetched DESIGN into this project:
cp -r /path/to/ulak-os/reports/current/design-references/<new-brand>/* ./reports/current/design-references/
```

Or switch reference entirely by editing the `## Reference brand` section above + re-running the design-system-architect agent to regenerate Master.

## Evolution discipline

This DESIGN.md is a **starting identity**, not a final verdict. After MVP launch, the product's actual design language will diverge based on:

- User research findings (who's actually using the product? what do they expect?)
- Accessibility audits
- Performance budget (web-vitals dimension from audit-scoring-framework)
- Brand decisions as the product matures

Record evolution in:
- `docs/architecture/design-evolution.md` — major design system changes with rationale + date
- `docs/adr/ADR-00X-design-system-direction.md` — when a design direction is set explicitly

## Anti-patterns the reference prevents

Starting from a disciplined brand reference inoculates against:

- **Generic AI-slop layout** — the default Tailwind + shadcn look without decisions
- **Random cards everywhere** — a brand teaches when NOT to card
- **Weak typography** — a reference has a scale; you inherit it
- **Weak spacing rhythm** — a reference has a unit; you inherit it
- **Fake-premium visuals** — disciplined brands don't lean on gradients + blur to feel premium

See `docs/runtime/anti-patterns.md` §Frontend / UX for the full list; the reference brand's DESIGN is a lens for catching these.

